panels.description: Duration that the current run of this pipeline has been in the Running state so far, in seconds. When a run completes, this stays at the duration of that run until the next run starts.
panels.title: Elapsed Time

panels.description: The total GB seconds for all persistent disk used by all workers associated with this Dataflow job.
panels.title: Total PD usage Time

panels.description: Estimated time in milliseconds spent running in the function of the ptransform totaled across threads on all workers of the job.
panels.title: Thread Time

panels.description: The amount of persistent disk currently being allocated to all workers associated with this Dataflow job.
panels.title: Disk Space capacity

panels.description: Pub/Sub Pull request latencies from PubsubIO.Read in Dataflow jobs. For Streaming Engine, this metric is deprecated. See the "Using the Dataflow monitoring interface" page for upcoming changes.
panels.title: Pub/Sub Pull Request Latencies

panels.description: The total bytes of streaming data processed by this Dataflow job.
panels.title: Total streaming data processed

panels.description: The total bytes of shuffle data processed by this Dataflow job
panels.title: Total shuffle data processed

panels.description: The total vCPU seconds used by this Dataflow job.
panels.title: Total vCPU time

panels.description: The number of vCPUs currently being used by this Dataflow job. This is the current number of workers times the number of vCPUs per worker.
panels.title: Current number of vCPUs in use

panels.description: Estimated memory used vs memory limit in bytes for the worker which uses the most memory in this Dataflow job. This chart can be used for debugging OOM (Out of Memory) issues.
panels.title: Memory utilization

panels.description: Estimated memory used vs memory limit in bytes for the worker which uses the most memory in this Dataflow job. This chart can be used for debugging OOM (Out of Memory) issues.
panels.title: Memory utilization

panels.description: The amount of memory currently being allocated to all workers associated with this Dataflow job.
panels.title: Memory capacity

panels.description: The number of elements produced by each PTransform
panels.title: Throughput

panels.description: The current maximum duration that an item of data has been processing or awaiting processing, in seconds.
panels.title: System lag

panels.description: The age (time since event timestamp) up to which all data has been processed by the pipeline.
panels.title: Data Freshness

panels.description: Number of log entries that contributed to user-defined metrics
panels.title: Worker Error Log count
